{
  "texts": [
    "Then, for almost all σ ∈ G e K, the following statement holds: for any finite extension L of K[σ] and any semiabelian variety A of positive dimension over L, the group A(L)/A(L) tor is a free Z-module of rank ℵ 0.",
    "We also investigate the Kummer-faithfulness of K(σ) and of K[σ].",
    "Ohtani showed that, if K is a number field and e ≥ 2, then any finite extension of K[σ] is Kummer-faithful for almost all σ ∈ G e K (see [Oht22, Corollary 1] and its corrigendum [Oht23, Corollary 1]).",
    "Our next result contains an improvement over the one by Ohtani, that is, we show that the same conclusion holds even if e = 1 for arbitrary finitely generated field K over Q.",
    "For the field K(σ), we obtain a partial result on its multiplicative group for any e ≥ 1."
  ]
}